        "timestamp": "2019-08-21 13:53:38.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Why do we need a ed branch instead of just creating elalto?\n\nI actually need to support 2 El Alto versions of these : one based on OpenDaylight Neon (current ODL release), and one based on OpenDaylight Fluorine (last release, still used by APPC).  I had created an 'ed' (early drop) branch and was going to use that, but was concerned there could be changes after the early drop versions I created that I'd miss, so instead I created new branches called \"elalto-fluorine\" based on the last change before the Neon port changes, and then I changed this change to use that new branch instead.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
